https://www.businesstimes.com.sg/stocks/hot-stock-rex-up-5-on-drone-technology-investmentThe oil and gas company said on Tuesday morning its investment comprises US$1 million for a 40 per cent interest in Singapore-incorporated drone company Xer Technologies. It also involves a commitment to inject up to US$3 million in the company  subject to the achievement of certain technical and sales milestones within the next 18 months.                                                                                                                                                       The acquisition is part of Rex International's efforts to diversify from its core business of oil exploration and production  and will "bring the group a step closer towards its approved business diversification mandate to include sustainable solutions for energy production and materials used in various industries"  the group said.Shares of Rex International were trading at 20.5 Singapore cents as at 10.08am on Tuesday  up 0.5 cent or 2.5 per cent.
